subSubSection.paragraph:
The prominent glandular ring of the posterior-most thoracic segments can be seen in the sections through the epidermis (
Fig. 5D
). The peristomial eyes are directly associated with the central nervous system and are located lateral to the cerebral ganglion (
Fig. 5E
). The single pair of nephridia, with a U-shaped duct, can be seen in the first thoracic segment (
Fig. 5E
).
